articles.description: Gibson Johnson and Sheriff Drammeh scored 13 apiece and Michael Thomas hit four free throws in the final 41 seconds to help Hawaii cool off UC Irvine 62-61 on Thursday night, ending the Anteaters' five-game win streak.
articles.headline: Hawaii outlasts UC Irvine 62-61

articles.description: Senior center Thomas Welch had 15 points and a career-high 17 rebounds and Aaron Holiday had 17 points and 10 assists to lead UCLA to a 75-68 victory over Oregon State on Thursday night.
articles.headline: Welch, Holiday lead UCLA past Oregon State 75-68

articles.description: Ryan Richardson scored eight of his 27 points in overtime and Weber State defeated Portland State 95-86 on Thursday night for its eighth straight win.
articles.headline: Richardson has 27, Weber St tops Portland St 95-86 in OT

articles.description: An Arizona cheerleader yelled into his megaphone while Arizona State's Remy Martin was shooting free throws, leading Pac-12 official Randy McCall to eject the cheerleader midway through the second half of Thursday's game.
articles.headline: Arizona cheerleader ejected for yelling into megaphone during free throws

images.name: Arizona vs. Arizona State (Mickey Mitchell drives on Arizona State forward Mickey Mitchell) [600x400]

articles.description: Frankie Ferrari made a key 3-pointer as part of a big San Francisco run late in the second half, and then added a clinching layup with 58.5 seconds remaining, and the Dons held on to beat No. 15 Saint Mary's 70-63 on Thursday.
articles.headline: San Francisco rallies to upset No. 15 Saint Mary's 70-63

images.caption: Jock Landale had 15-first half points, but fails to get the easy two when he misses the slam dunk down low.
images.name: Landale clanks dunk off iron

articles.description: Emmanuel Ndumanya scored a career-high 23 points, pulled down 10 rebounds and Josip Vrankic tossed in 19 points in Santa Clara's 81-72 win at Portland Thursday night.
articles.headline: Ndumanya scores 23 as Santa Clara holds off Portland 81-72

videos.description: SMU's Jarry Foster misses wide open dunk attempt then Shaqquan Aaron throws it down at the other end.
videos.headline: Crazy sequence leads to USC's Aaron dunk

videos.description: Shake Milton lobs the alley-oop to a flying Jarrey Foster and he soars to throw it down.
videos.headline: Foster climbs the ladder on dunk

videos.description: Chimezie Metu jab steps and then takes flight for a nasty one-hand jam on three SMU defenders.
videos.headline: USC's Metu puts three defenders on poster

videos.description: Shake Milton finds Ben Emelogu cutting backdoor for the alley-oop hammer.
videos.headline: SMU's Emelogu brings the house down with dunk

videos.description: Shake Milton leans into the defender looking to get a foul call and drills the jumper as the shot clock expires.
videos.headline: SMU's Milton makes tough shot

videos.description: Shake Milton gets the ball again as the shot clock is winding down and he hits a tough floater with a defender all over him.
videos.headline: Everything going in for SMU's Milton

videos.description: Shake Milton delivers a pinpoint pass to to Jimmy Whitt and he skies for the jam.
videos.headline: SMU doing its best version of 'lob city'

videos.description: Shake Milton finds Jason Whitt again on the alley-oop and he slams it down.
videos.headline: SMU's Milton-Whitt connection does it again
